  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Hotel Orsa Maggiore is a charming family-run boutique hotel. The swimming pool sits pride of place, surrounded by a smart sun deck with loungers. Indulge, with an Aperol spritz aperitif from the poolside bar before choosing a table for dinner. Seafood is a speciality – think swordfish carpaccio and grilled mahi-mahi. If you fancy a trip to the beach, the picturesque black sands of Sabbie Nere are 5 minutes’ walk away. It is a great base for exploring the rest of the <a data-udi="umb://document/c2a0cfb0af8146d18a45e08bc4c22d42" href="/{localLink:umb://document/c2a0cfb0af8146d18a45e08bc4c22d42}" title="Aeolian Islands">Aeolian Islands</a>, with good transport links for day trips to the other islands. The bedrooms provide a fresh and tranquil retreat after days spent exploring the volcanic archipelago. </p>
<p>Transfer time: approx. 1 hour 45 mins by private car to Milazzo Port from Catania Airport; approx. 1 hour 40 by hydrofoil/ferry to Vulcano Port &amp; approx 10 mins by hotel shuttle to Hotel Orsa Maggiore</p>
<p>* Please note that the ferry ticket to the island is payable locally for approx. €20 per person one way</p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
